South Africans now have the option of a green death. Instead of being cremated or buried, you can opt for a process called aquamation. CAPE TOWN - South Africans now have the option of a green death. Instead of being cremated or buried, you can opt for a process called aquamation. The environmentally friendly process has been launched in Cape Town. It saves 90 percent more energy than fire-based cremation. Globally, aquamation is considered a cleaner process. And with cemeteries running out of space, it seems a wise option.